So, some calculations.

Power usage is 10/h + 5/h * crew capacity, i.e. 15, 20, or 25/h.

Oxygen usage is 1 * number of kerbals, i.e. 1, 2, or 3/h.

CO2 generation is the same as oxygen generation.

Most pods can survive for 100h. Exceptions are the lander cans (150h) and cockpits (50h!), as well as the hitchhiker container (500h!).

Time to lack of power is as follows:

Cupola: 13.3h

Mk 1 Lander Can, Mk 1 & 2 Cockpits, Command Pod Mk 1: 3.3h!

Mk 3 Cockpit, Mk 1-2 command pod: 6h

Mk 2 Lander Can: 5h

Hitchhiker container: 10h

What does this mean? Basically, as follows:

If you're doing anything more than building something to rendezvous with a space station, you'll need some sort of power storage or generation. Almost anything will do, however. Even the flat solar panel is overkill. (Theoretically, you could keep 90 hitchhiker containers powered with one solar panel, or 360 kerbals).

Beyond about 100h, you'll start needing extra oxygen. As far as I can tell, you should put in a LS-19A if you have any more than a LS-O2A tank, and you should replace it with the LS-32C if you have beyond about ~5000 oxygen. (Although note that the LS-19A can only supply 2 kerbals). (A LS-19A effectively doubles your oxygen; a LS-32C effectively triples it)

Also, a tip. Put a LS-IA on your booster and it will refill the tank in the LS-19A/LS-O2A on your ascent.

I painstakingly implemented the values for food, oxygen and water according to the math in this post http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/entry.php/457-Life-Support-Mathematics-How-much-food-water-and-oxygen-do-Kerbals-need.

Note that the requirements should be doubled as the initial kerbal body mass was off.

I made it so a days resources was one "unit", and the kerbals consumed one unit per 24 hours. It is pretty hard to do when the number is in resource consumption per seconds, at least for me as I am hardly a mathamagician. I have it around 1.1 per day currently.

The way I adjusted things was to normalize the density in the resource cfg to match the density of a days supply (at least I think I did, that was yesterday). I'll post the values if anyone is curious.

One thing that is very evident is a kerbal needs 1/10 the compressed oxygen as currently implimented in the mod. However, water and food presents its own challanges as they cannot be recycled and are either heavy (water) or voluminous (food). You have to bring it with you!

I have been doing research on how they did it for Apollo (8-12 days). They had plenty of food in the pantries, in fact they usually didnt eat all of it because it was always tastey. Power, oxygen and water was came from the 3 fuel cells in the Service module, it combined hydrogen and oxygen to produce electricity and water, and the same oxygen tanks provided an abundant supply. Even when one of two oxygen tanks burst on Apollo 13, oxygen was never a problem, it was CO2 build up, lack of electricity, and lack of water that they were worried about.

Now, I like the idea of a fuel cell in the first post, but I I'd have to be careful to not accidentally eat all my rocket fuel making water and power! I might repurpose the RTG for a efficent fuel cell that produced water and breathing oxygen from LOX and LH, and KSPX has great sized tanks for that.
